div1.p: The return of Geo. F. Thomas Sheriff of Walla Walla County Washington Territory to the Writ of Habeas Corpus hereto annexed.

In obedience to the Writ of Habeas Corpus hereto annexed I do hereby certify and return to the District Court of the First Judicial District of Washington Territory that before coming of said Writ to me to Wit on the 29th day of August 1878 at Walla Walla Washington Territory the said John Morrisey mentioned in said Writ was placed in my custody among other prisoners by virtue of a commitment issued by C.P. Lacy Esq. one of the Justices of the Peace in and for Walla Walla County W.T. on a charge of Grand Larcery and that the said John Morrisey remains now in my custody by virtue of said commitment a copy of which is hereto annexed and made a part of this return and I have here his body before the said District Court as by the said Writ I am commanded
Geo F. Thomas Sheriff Walla Walla County by JB Thompson Deputy
